The US administration condemns Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro's use of foreign military personnel, specifically Russian military personnel and equipment, to stay in power. The administration believes that Maduro will use this military support to further repress the Venezuelan people, worsen the economic crisis, and endanger regional stability. They call on the Venezuelan military to fulfill its duty to protect the citizens of Venezuela. The US administration also warns against the deployment of military assets by external actors in Venezuela or elsewhere in the Western Hemisphere, considering it a direct threat to international peace and security in the region. They reaffirm their commitment to defending and protecting the interests of the United States and its partners in the Western Hemisphere, based on shared values of liberty, security, and the rule of law.